{
  "texts": [
    "From left to right, if [z] ≃ ̸ ∈ X ≃ ⊃ ≃ Y ≃, then there is a [z ′] ≃ ⊑ ≃ [z] ≃ such that [z ′] ≃ ∈ X ≃ but [z ′] ≃ ̸ ∈ Y ≃, so z ′ ∈ X but z ′ ̸ ∈ Y, so z ′ ̸ ∈ X ⊃ Y.",
    "Since [z ′] ≃ ⊑ ≃ [z] ≃, we have z ′ ⊑ s z.",
    "Finally, since X ⊃ Y ∈ RO(F), z ′ ̸ ∈ X ⊃ Y and z ′ ⊑ s z together imply z ̸ ∈ X ⊃ Y by Fact 4.2, so [z] ≃ ̸ ∈ (X ⊃ Y) ≃.",
    "For (iii), from right to left, if [x] ≃ ̸ ∈ (■ i X) ≃, so x ̸ ∈ ■ i X, then there is a y ∈ S such that xR i y and y ̸ ∈ X, which implies[x] ≃ R ≃ i [y] ≃ and [y] ≃ ̸ ∈ X ≃, so [x] ≃ ̸ ∈ ■ ≃ i X ≃.",
    "From left to right, if [x] ≃ ̸ ∈ ■ ≃ i X ≃, then there is a [y] ≃ ∈ S ≃ such that [x] ≃ R ≃ i [y] ≃ and [y] ≃ ̸ ∈ X ≃."
  ]
}